description:
Directorate of Intelligence Style Manual &amp; Writers Guide for Intelligence Publications, Eighth Edition, 2011. Style Manual from the Directorate of Intelligence, a part of the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA), OCR'd for your convenience. Made available on Feb. 28, 2012 through the efforts of the legal nonprofit National Security Counselors, following a Freedom of Information Act request.

- from the Preface:
&quot;In dealing with foreign policy and national security, our government has many sources of insight on which to draw. The depth of our knowledge, the strength of our thinking, and the power of our words will ensure that our customers, from policymakers to operations officers, continue to rely on the Directorate of Intelligence.&quot;
